selectedCommunities.name: Kali Yoga (KY)
selectedCommunities.description: Kali Mudra is practiced in Restorative Yoga Sequences, or Therapy Yoga Sequences for healing symptoms related to anxiety, depression, or insomnia. The most important aspect of the practice of Kali mudra is that it encourages positivity in the body while clearing blockages in the sushumna nadi (channel), thus reducing tensions and distractions. This mudra is also referred to as Ksepana Mudra which is a gesture of pouring out and letting go. It is mainly practiced as part of meditation or pranayama, but can also be adopted in the asana practices. In Kali Mudra all the fingers except the index fingers interlock, with the palms facing each other, and while the fingers interlock, the left thumb rests over the right thumb and not vice versa.
